XmlDocumentationCommentExample(Int32, Int32)

Compares two numbers to determine if they are the same.

Declaration
public static bool XmlDocumentationCommentExample(int numberOne, int numberTwo)
Parameters
Type Name Description
System.Int32 numberOne

The first number.
System.Int32 numberTwo

The second number.
Returns
Type Description
System.Boolean

A boolean of true or false.
Remarks

This method needs two things:

  1. A number
  2. Another number

Numbers to be compared must:

  • Be >= zero
  • Be less than 100
  • Not be an even number

Keep in mind:

NumberValidity
1Valid.
2Invalid
200Invalid

For more information please review the Abatab Documentation Project.

Examples

Here is an example of the code:

if(numberOne == numberTwo)
{
    return true;
}
else
{
    return false;
}
